biography.bio: Douglas MacLean was born on January 10, 1890 in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, USA as Charles Douglas MacLean. He was an actor and producer, known for Introduce Me (1925), Hold That Lion (1926) and Going Up (1923). He was married to Florence Barton, Barbara Barondess, Lorraine MacLean and Faith Cole. He died on July 9, 1967 in Beverly Hills, Los Angeles, California, USA.
biography.name: Douglas MacLean

biography.bio: Beatrice Burnham was born on October 3, 1897 in El Paso, Texas, USA. She is an actress, known for Riders of the Purple Sage (1925), Hitchin' Posts (1920) and Diamonds Adrift (1921).
biography.name: Beatrice Burnham

biography.bio: Walt Whitman was born on April 25, 1859 in Lyon, New York, USA. He was an actor, known for The Mark of Zorro (1920), The Hopper (1918) and The Tar Heel Warrior (1917). He died on March 27, 1928 in Santa Monica, California, USA.
biography.name: Walt Whitman

biography.bio: Margaret Livingston was born on November 25, 1900 in Salt Lake City, Utah, USA. She is known for her work on Sunrise (1927), Smart Money (1931) and Through the Breakers (1928). She was married to Paul Whiteman. She died on December 13, 1984 in Warrington, Pennsylvania, USA.
biography.name: Margaret Livingston

biography.bio: Wade Boteler was born on October 3, 1888 in Santa Ana, California, USA. He was an actor and writer, known for The Green Hornet Strikes Again! (1940), The Green Hornet (1940) and The Painted Desert (1931). He was married to Ellen Evelyn James. He died on May 7, 1943 in Hollywood, Los Angeles, California.
biography.name: Wade Boteler

biography.bio: Mary Jane Irving was born on October 20, 1913 in Columbia, South Carolina, USA. She was an actress, known for The Godless Girl (1929), The Good Bad Boy (1924) and Will You Be Staying for Supper? (1919). She was married to Robert Carson. She died on July 17, 1983 in Los Angeles, California, USA.
biography.name: Mary Jane Irving

biography.bio: Charles Hill Mailes was born on May 25, 1870 in Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada. He was an actor, known for The Mark of Zorro (1920), The New York Hat (1912) and For His Son (1912). He was married to Claire McDowell. He died on February 17, 1937 in Los Angeles, California, USA.
biography.name: Charles Hill Mailes

biography.bio: Mollie McConnell was born on September 24, 1865 in Chicago, Illinois, USA. She was an actress, known for The Twin Triangle (1916), St. Elmo (1914) and His Old-Fashioned Dad (1917). She was married to William A. McConnell and Sherwood MacDonald. She died on December 9, 1920 in Los Angeles, California, USA.
biography.name: Mollie McConnell

biography.bio: Jack Singleton is an actor, known for Dry Up (1925), Al's Troubles (1926) and Going Good (1925).
biography.name: Jack Singleton

biography.bio: Joseph Bennett was born on August 28, 1894 in Los Angeles, California, USA. He was an actor, known for Youth's Desire (1920), The Golden Fleece (1918) and Love Never Dies (1921). He died on December 3, 1931 in Hollywood, California.
biography.name: Joseph Bennett

biography.bio: George Holmes was born on November 25, 1918 in Shamokin, Pennsylvania, USA. He was an actor, known for Dark Alibi (1946), The Man in the Trunk (1942) and The Falcon in San Francisco (1945). He died on February 19, 1985 in Los Angeles, California, USA.
biography.name: George Holmes
